text.tspan: Starting Tails from the top canvas frame provides the
most customizable experience, as it allows people to
circumvent dealing with any settings configuration and
moves them forward using Tails’ default settings.
Starting Tails from the top canvas frame also presents
an
opportunity for the settings to be hidden/collapsed
since ‘Start Tails’ is now removed from the settings
configuration flow.

Starting Tails from the bottom of the canvas provides
the most logical settings configuration experience, as it
presents the ‘Start Tails’ button at the end of a linear
configuration flow.
This location is most appropriate if the ‘Start Tails’
button can stand alone as the only way to move away
from this screen. However, this location would also
work if there is a close[x] located in the top canvas frame
that moves people back to the Tails boot screen when
clicked, though there is some imbalance in the compari
son of these two locations given their intended function.
